node_modules/
.DS_Store
*.log
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# Dev-mode scratch: when running the bridge from the framework repo,
# the spine is created here. The framework repo never commits dev state.
template/.maddu/
.maddu/*
# …but the architecture CONTRACT is a committed team artifact (like CODEOWNERS):
# it must ship so the architecture-drift gate enforces on a fresh checkout / CI.
!.maddu/config/
.maddu/config/*
!.maddu/config/architecture.json
# The pinned CI gate profile is likewise a committed team artifact: it must
# ship so `maddu ci` enforces the SAME required set on a fresh checkout / CI
# runner as it does locally (the churn-proof contract, docs/46-ci.md).
!.maddu/config/ci.json
# The verdict-machinery pin set is the same kind of committed team artifact: it must ship so
# tracked-source-drift enforces the SAME pinned files on a fresh checkout / CI
# runner. Left ignored it would be invisible to every PR diff and every CI job,
# and the gate would silently report "no tracked sources configured" — green over
# nothing.
!.maddu/config/tracked-sources.json
# Likewise the structural-mass baseline (the monolith ratchet floor) must ship so
# the architecture-mass gate enforces "monoliths may only shrink" in CI.
!.maddu/state/
.maddu/state/*
!.maddu/state/architecture/
.maddu/state/architecture/*
!.maddu/state/architecture/mass-baseline.json
.omc/

# Brand and marketing assets are NOT part of the public repo.
# Local copies are fine; do not commit them.
brand/
marketing/

# Local agent-instruction files at the repo ROOT only (anchored with a leading
# slash so the SHIPPED worker brief template/maddu/CLAUDE.md stays tracked).
# These are workstation-local and must never be swept in by `git add -A`.
/AGENTS.md
/CLAUDE.md

# Competitive-research working artifacts (2026-07) — deep-research agent
# outputs + diff synthesis contain unverified third-party claims; kept
# local until manually verified. Brief lives in marketing/ (tracked or not
# at operator's discretion).
docs/research/*.pdf
docs/research/competitive-analysis-diff-2026-07.md
docs/research/competitive-response-proposal.md

# Internal working docs — not published (operator decision 2026-07-06).
# The three JSON files below the ignore are load-bearing: release-parity /
# audit-ledger-coherent / governance-budget gates read them on fresh clones.
docs/audit/*
!docs/audit/FIXED-IN.json
!docs/audit/LEDGER.json
!docs/audit/governance-budget.json
docs/research/
docs/sessions/
docs/releases/
*.torrent
